{"type":"message","id":"19e2e646","parentId":"a210a745","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:27:51.174Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9n0mvf0uphbq_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5792\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2816\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\n[mutation proposed] the\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 022717 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment requires a concrete implementation to test the hypothesis that causal structure equals invariant structure. The pulse logs exist but need a classifier to extract and measure invariants.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"fresh-gulf","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5792\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2816\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\n[mutation proposed] the\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 022717 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment requires a concrete implementation to test the hypothesis that causal structure equals invariant structure. The pulse logs exist but need a classifier to extract and measure invariants.\n","name":"powershell C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774333671172}}
{"type":"message","id":"25b9980f","parentId":"19e2e646","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:27:51.175Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9n0mvf0uphbq_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 022618\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. There's a key insight about COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY that needs to be explored\r\n3. The next action is the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n4. The pending actions include implementing TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nLooking at the notes, the most concrete next step would be to start implementing the TIC experiment. Let me check what files exist that I can work with.\r\n\r\nThe pulse log mentioned is: `pulse_2026-03-24 022415.md` in the `logs/` directory.\r\n\r\nI should:\r\n1. First look at existing pulse logs to understand their format\r\n2. Create a TIC classifier implementation\r\n3. Document the experiment design\r\n\r\nSince I'm stateless, I need to be specific about what file edit to make. Let me create a concrete action that advances the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step would be to implement the TIC classifier or set up the experiment. Let me create a Python script for the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pending items:\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe most concrete first action would be to implement the TIC classifier. Let me create a `tic/classifier.py` or similar that implements the temporal invariance compression algorithm.\r\n\r\nLet me make a concrete file edit to start the TIC experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight provides a clear path forward: implement Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) to classify pulse content as invariant or variant, then test if invariants predict next-pulse content. The pulse logs in `logs/` are the dataset.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier implementation - a Python script that processes pulse logs to extract temporal invariants (content patterns that persist across sessions) vs variants (session-specific content), and measures classification accuracy.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n\r\n## Concept\r\nCausal structure = invariant structure. A compressor that discovers what stays the same across temporal gaps has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n## Algorithm\r\n\r\n```python\r\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC Classifier - Tests COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis\r\n\"\"\"\r\nimport re\r\nimport os\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\ndef extract_content(pulse_file):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract meaningful content from pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    text = pulse_file.read_text()\r\n    # Remove timestamps, metadata\r\n    content = re.sub(r'^\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2.*', '', text, flags=re.MULTILINE)\r\n    content = re.sub(r'```.*?```', '', content, flags=re.DOTALL)  # Remove code blocks\r\n    return content.strip()\r\n\r\ndef tokenize(text):\r\n    \"\"\"Simple word-level tokenization.\"\"\"\r\n    return re.findall(r'\\b\\w+\\b', text.lower())\r\n\r\ndef compute_ngrams(tokens, n=2):\r\n    \"\"\"Compute n-gram frequency distribution.\"\"\"\r\n    ngrams = ['_'.join(tokens[i:i+n]) for i in range(len(tokens)-n+1)]\r\n    return Counter(ngrams)\r\n\r\ndef extract_invariants(pulse_files):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract content that persists across ALL pulses (potential causal structure).\"\"\"\r\n    all_ngrams = []\r\n    for pf in pulse_files:\r\n        content = extract_content(pf)\r\n        tokens = tokenize(content)\r\n        all_ngrams.append(compute_ngrams(tokens, n=2))\r\n    \r\n    # Invariant = ngram appears in ALL pulse files\r\n    if not all_ngrams:\r\n        return []\r\n    \r\n    intersection = all_ngrams[0]\r\n    for ngrams in all_ngrams[1:]:\r\n        intersection &= ngrams  # Set intersection\r\n    \r\n    return list(intersection.keys())\r\n\r\ndef classify_content(pulse_file, invariants):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify pulse content as invariant (causal) or variant (accidental).\"\"\"\r\n    content = extract_content(pulse_file)\r\n    tokens = tokenize(content)\r\n    ngrams = compute_ngrams(tokens, n=2)\r\n    \r\n    invariant_count = sum(1 for ng in ngrams if ng in invariants)\r\n    total_count = sum(ngrams.values())\r\n    \r\n    if total_count == 0:\r\n        return 'empty', 0.0\r\n    \r\n    ratio = invariant_count / total_count\r\n    return ('invariant' if ratio > 0.5 else 'variant', ratio)\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(current_invariants, future_pulse):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict if future pulse maintains invariant structure.\"\"\"\r\n    classification, ratio = classify_content(future_pulse, current_invariants)\r\n    return classification == 'invariant'\r\n\r\ndef run_experiment():\r\n    \"\"\"Run TIC experiment on pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    logs_dir = Path('logs')\r\n    pulse_files = sorted(logs_dir.glob('pulse_*.md'))\r\n    \r\n    if len(pulse_files) < 3:\r\n        print(f\"Need at least 3 pulse files, found {len(pulse_files)}\")\r\n        return\r\n    \r\n    # Split: training (first 80%) vs test (last 20%)\r\n    split_idx = int(len(pulse_files) * 0.8)\r\n    train_files = pulse_files[:split_idx]\r\n    test_files = pulse_files[split_idx:]\r\n    \r\n    print(f\"Training: {len(train_files)} pulses\")\r\n    print(f\"Testing: {len(test_files)} pulses\")\r\n    \r\n    # Phase 1: Extract invariants from training set\r\n    invariants = extract_invariants(train_files)\r\n    print(f\"\\nInvariants found: {len(invariants)}\")\r\n    print\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 02:26:49\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774333671174}}
